   [meetings.gif]

   The following are some of the scheduled computing meetings of possible
   interest:

   [red_ball.gif] U.S. ATLAS Computing Meeting: A monthly phone/VRVS
   conference. Subscribe to the U.S. ATLAS computing mailing list
   (usatlas-computing-l) for info. Every fourth Wednesday at 1pm eastern.

   [red_ball.gif] U.S. ATLAS Grid Software Meeting: A monthly phone/VRVS
   conference. Subscribe to the U.S. ATLAS grid mailing list
   (usatlas-grid-l) for info. Every fourth Wednesday at 1pm eastern,
   alternating bi-weekly with the U.S. ATLAS Computing Meeting.

   [red_ball.gif] ATLAS Weekly Software and Simulation Meeting: Every
   Thursday, 1600 - 1800 hours at CERN (10:00 am EDT). This meeting can be
   followed on VRVS in the Moon virtual room.

   [red_ball.gif] ATLAS Software Weeks: Roughly quarterly, and usually at
   CERN. Consult the ATLAS meeting schedule on the ATLAS web.

